Laura Holgate has been nominated by President Obama to serve as Ambassador and U.S. Representative to the Vienna Office of the United Nations and the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA). She has over 14 years of experience in senior positions across the U.S. Government and has advised the President for over six years as Special Assistant to the President and Senior Director for WMD Terrorism and Threat Reduction on the National Security Council staff. Throughout her career, she has focused on preventing states and terrorists from acquiring and using weapons of mass destruction. She has played a key role in the Nuclear Security Summit, leading efforts to strengthen global nuclear security and prevent nuclear smuggling. She also led the effort to destroy Syria's chemical weapons stockpile and launched the Global Health Security Agenda. Her exceptional leadership and expertise make her highly qualified for this role.